[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. Sicilian Defense, Old Sicilian Variation"]
[Black "Old Sicilian Variation (6)"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 { Sicilian Defense } 2. Nf3 Nc6 { Old Sicilian Variation } 3. c3
{ Preparing d4. } 3... e5 4. d4 { Challenging Black's center. } 4... exd4 5.
Bc4 { Sacrificing a pawn in order to get a lead in development. } 5... dxc3
{ This poor move wins a pawn, but opens up the d-file for the Queen to join the attack. }
6. Nxc3 { Capturing the pawn first while developing a piece. } 6... Be7
{ A very poor move. } 7. Qd5
{ Centralizing the Queen, threatening checkmate on  f7  . } 7... d6
{ Creating an escape square for the King.   Note that  7...Nh6  would lose to  8.Bxh6  gxh6  9.Qxf7#  . }
8. Qxf7+
{ Winning the pawn back with check. Black's King is in serious trouble @@StartBracket@@+7.0@@EndBracket@@. White has a lot of good moves available to keep the attack going. }
