4. Nxd4 { Open Variation } 4... g6 { Accelerated Dragon Variation } 5. Nc3
{ Modern Variation } 5... Bg7 { Attacking the Knight in the center. } 6. Be3
{ Defending the Knight. } 6... e6
{ A very poor move, creating a hole in the position on  d6  . } 7. Ndb5
{ Only the fourth most popular move, but definitely the best one. And it's the move with the highest winrate by far!   From this point, Black has a wide range of moves. But if you know that the engine suggests moves like  7...Kf8  and  7...h6  , you know that Black's position is bad @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7... Bxc3+ { One of Black's most common moves. } 8. bxc3
{ Recapturing with the pawn in order to keep the possibility of Nd6+. } 8... d5
{ The most popular move. } 9. exd5
{ A practical solution.   9.Bc5  is the top choice of Stockfish 13, but things will get very complicated... }
9... exd5 10. Qxd5 { A nice temporary Queen sacrifice! } 10... Qxd5 11. Nc7+
{ A family fork, forking King, Queen and Rook. White is up a pawn and has the Bishop pair @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@. }
