[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 { Sicilian Defense } 2. Nf3 Nc6 { Old Sicilian Variation } 3. d4 cxd4
4. Nxd4 { Open Variation } 4... g6 { Accelerated Dragon Variation } 5. Nc3
{ Modern Variation } 5... Bg7 { Attacking the Knight in the center. } 6. Be3
{ Defending the Knight. } 6... a6
{ This blunder was played in almost 10,000 games! } 7. Nd5
{ ...but only in less than 5% of the games, White was able to find the best move. }
7... e6
{ Trying to kick the Knight back.   7...Nf6  8.Nxc6  bxc6?  , and Black's Queen is trapped after  9.Bb6  @@StartBracket@@+6.5@@EndBracket@@.   After  7...Nxd4  8.Bxd4  Bxd4  9.Qxd4  Nf6  10.Nb6  Rb8  11.e5  , White totally dominates the position @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Nxc6 { Trading a pair of Knights. } 8... bxc6 9. Bb6
{ The reason why Nd5 was that strong! } 9... Qh4
{ Black's best move, attacking the pawn on  e4  . } 10. Nc7+
{ Check, forking King and Rook in the corner. } 10... Kf8 11. Bc5+
{ A zwischenzug in order to improve the position of the dark-squared Bishop. }
11... Ne7 12. Nxa8 { Grabbing a free Rook. } 12... Qxe4+ 13. Qe2
{ White is up a Rook for a pawn while Black's King lost his right to castle @@StartBracket@@+6.0@@EndBracket@@. }
