7. Bd2
{ Defending the Knight on  c3  while unpinning it, and keeping an eye on Black's Queen behind it. }
7... Bb4
{ Increasing the pressure on  c3  . This most played move actually is a blunder! }
8. a3 { Attacking the Bishop on  b4  . } 8... Bxc3
{ Trading minor pieces.   8...Be7  would fail to  9.Nd5  , with a discovered attack on the Queen. }
9. Bxc3 { Attacking the Queen. } 9... Qb6 10. Nd6+
{ Checking the King. Black will now lose his castling rights. White has the Bishop pair, while Black's light-squared Bishop is locked in @@StartBracket@@+5.5@@EndBracket@@. }
