7... d4 { Attacking the Knight on  c3  , gaining more space in the center. } 8.
Nd5
{ A popular blunder. White's problem is that the pawn on  e4  has two jobs at the same time: Defending both Knights.   After a move like  8.Ne2  , Black completely dominates the center @@StartBracket@@-3.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8... Bxf5
{ Removing one of the Knights.   9.exf5  would lose to  9...Qxd5  @@StartBracket@@-7.5@@EndBracket@@. }
9. Bxf6 { Trying to complicate the position. } 9... gxf6
{ Recapturing the Bishop with the pawn. Black won a piece @@StartBracket@@-5.0@@EndBracket@@!   Black's Queen has to keep an eye on the Knight on  d5  , in case of  10.exf5  Qxd5  @@StartBracket@@-7.5@@EndBracket@@. }
