1. e4 c5 { Sicilian Defense } 2. Nf3 e6 { French Variation } 3. Nc3 b6
{ Create a square for the light-squared Bishop to develop. A suboptimal move. }
4. d4
{ Challenging Black's center, with the idea to push the pawn to  d5  and block the diagonal once Black's Bishop fianchettos. }
4... Bb7
{ Continuing with the plan to fianchetto the Bishop, another poor move. } 5. d5
{ Blocking the Bishop's diagonal. } 5... exd5
{ Trading a pair of center pawns. } 6. exd5 Nf6
{ Increasing the pressure on  d5  , a blunder. } 7. d6
{ White now no longer has the intention to block the diagonal for the Bishop on  b7  . Instead, his plan will be to win material, probably after Qe2+ next move @@StartBracket@@+6.0@@EndBracket@@. }
