Bc5 { Paulsen-Basman Defense, A rather dubious move. } 5. Nc3 Qf6
{ Trying a cheap checkmate on  f2  while attacking the Knight on  d4  . This is a very bad move... }
6. Be3
{ Developing the dark-squared Bishop while defending the Knight and the pawn on  f2  . Black is already behind in development. }
6... e5 { The second most popular move, but not a good one! } 7. Nd5
{ Attacking the Queen while threatening a fork on  c7  .   7.Ndb5  is the best move according to the engine, but  7.Nd5  has the highest winrate in practice. }
7... Qd8 { Bringing the Queen into safety while defending  c7  . } 8. Nb5
{ Threatening a Knight fork on  c7  again, while attacking the Bishop on  c5  . }
8... Bxe3 { Black tries to exchange a pair of minor pieces. } 9. Ndc7+
{ The most accurate move, giving a check and opening the d-file for the Queen to join the attack. }
9... Kf8 10. Qd6+
{ Checking Black's King. White will capture the Bishop on  e3  later, equalizing material. White is dominating the position while most of Black's pieces are still on their starting square @@StartBracket@@+7.5@@EndBracket@@. }
