6. f4 { Levenfish Variation, Preparing an aggressive pawn push. } 6... Bg7
{ 6...Nc6  is a less risky move, because it prevents White from playing  e5  @@StartBracket@@+0.0@@EndBracket@@. }
7. e5
{ Attacking the Knight on  f6  .   Stockfish likes other moves too in this position, e.g.  7.Bb5  . But  7.e5  will probably give you the best results in practice. }
7... dxe5
{ 7...Nh5  is a solid reply.  8.g4  isn't a good idea because of  8...Nxf4  9.Bxf4  dxe5  , forking two of White's minor pieces @@StartBracket@@-2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8. fxe5 { Attacking the Knight on  f6  once again. } 8... Ng4
