1. e4 c5 { Sicilian Defense } 2. Nf3 d6 { Modern Variation } 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4
Nf6 5. Nc3 g6
{ Dragon Variation, With the idea to fianchetto the dark-squared Bishop next move. }
6. Bc4 { Developing the Bishop, with the idea to castle next move. } 6... Bg7
7. O-O O-O 8. f4
{ This blunder has been played over 1,000 times! But only 1 in 3 Black players knew how to punish White's mistake. }
8... Qb6 { Attacking the Knight on  d4  while pinning it to the King. } 9. Kh1
{ Stepping out of the pin. } 9... Nxe4
{ A temporary Knight sacrifice in order to open up the diagonal for the Bishop. Note that the Knight on  d4  now has been attacked twice. }
10. Nxe4
{ Accepting the sacrifice.   10.Be3  is the alternative, but after  10...Nxc3  11.bxc3  Qc7  , Black is better @@StartBracket@@-2.5@@EndBracket@@. }
10... Qxd4 { Offering a trade of Queens is best. } 11. Qxd4 Bxd4
{ Black won a pawn with this nice tactic @@StartBracket@@-2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
