{ Attacking one of the defenders of the pawn on  d4  while pinning it to the Queen. }
7. Be2 { Unpinning the Knight while defending it. } 7... Bxf3
{ Removing one of the defenders of  d4  . Not the best move, because Black no longer has a Bishop pair. }
8. Bxf3 { Not only attacking the Queen, but also the Knight behind her! } 8...
Qxd4
{ Black removed one of the defenders of  d4  last move, so he can grab the  d4  pawn for free now! Right? }
9. Bxc6+
{ The Knight on  c6  was defending the Queen on  d4  . By capturing the Knight with a check, Black's Queen suddenly is no longer defended! }
9... bxc6 10. Qxd4
{ White is up a whole Queen for a single pawn, Black is lost @@StartBracket@@+10.5@@EndBracket@@.  This variation is very similar to theScandinavian Defense, Modern Variation and theNimzowitsch Defense, Scandinavian Variation. }
