1. e4 c5 { Sicilian Defense } 2. c3 { Alapin Variation, Preparing d4. } 2...
Nc6
{ This dubious move is by far the most played move in the lichess database, but it has almost never been played by experts. }
3. d4 { Seizing the center! } 3... cxd4 { Trading a pair of center pawns. } 4.
cxd4 g6
{ Black wants to fianchetto his Bishop, but that will take too much time!   If Black choses to play  4...Nf6??  , White should continue with the same moves:  5.d5  Ne5  6.f4  @@StartBracket@@+2.5@@EndBracket@@. }
5. d5 { Chasing away the Knight on  c6  . } 5... Ne5
{ 5...Nb8  is the best move, but most players don't want to play it @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6. f4
{ Attacking the Knight once again. The Knight is trapped and will be lost soon @@StartBracket@@+4.5@@EndBracket@@! If Black hadn't played 4... g6, he would still have that square available to escape. }
