1. e4 c5 { Sicilian Defense } 2. c3 { Alapin Variation, Preparing d4. } 2...
Nc6
{ This dubious move is by far the most played move in the lichess database, but it has almost never been played by experts. }
3. d4 { Seizing the center! } 3... cxd4 { Trading a pair of center pawns. } 4.
cxd4 e6
{ Opening the diagonal for the Bishop on  f8  , while preparing a d5- push. }
5. d5
{ White pushes the pawn to  d5  himself and attacks the Knight on  c6  in order to gain space and to keep the initiative. }
5... exd5 { Trading a pair of center pawns. } 6. exd5
{ Renewing the threat to capture the Knight on  c6  . } 6... Nce7
{ This blunder has been played hundreds of times!   6...Qa5  is another bad move. Stockfish 13 really hates Black's position after  7.Nc3  @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@.   6...Ne5  or  6...Bb4+  are playable alternatives @@StartBracket@@+0.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7. d6
{ Pushing the pawn forward for the third time, attacking the Knight once again. }
7... Nc6
{ 7...Qa5+  should be met with  8.Nc3  . One line goes like this:  8...Qe5+  9.Be2  Nf5  10.Nb5  Bxd6  11.Nf3  @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Qe2+
{ Black has to block this check with a piece on  e7  , but that square is defended by the pawn on  d6  @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@. }
