dxc3 { Smith-Morra Gambit Accepted } 4. Nxc3 g6 5. Nf3 Bg7 6. Bc4
{ Keeping an eye on  f7  . } 6... e6
{ Blocking the diagonal for White's Bishop, but creating a hole in the defense on  d6  . }
7. Nb5 { Heading to  d6  with check. } 7... d5
{ The most common defense, covering  d6  with the Queen while challenging White's center. }
