{ According to the engine,  9.Bf4  is the best move, giving up the Bishop on  c4  @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@.   But I prefer to keep it simple with  9.Qxd5  @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@.   9.Bxd5  fails to  9...Qa5+  , pushing all of White's pieces back:  10.Nc3  Ne7  11.Bb3  @@StartBracket@@+0.0@@EndBracket@@. }
9... Qxd5 { Exchanging Queens. } 10. Nc7+
