1. e4 e6 { French Defense } 2. d4 { Normal Variation } 2... d5 3. Nc3
{ Paulsen Variation } 3... dxe4 { Rubinstein Variation } 4. Nxe4 Nf6
{ This move was played the most.   4...Nd7  would have been a bit better, preparing  Ngf6  . The point is that after White captures on  f6  , Black now can recapture on  f6  with the Knight instead of with the Queen. }
5. Nxf6+ Qxf6 6. Nf3
{ Developing a piece.   The move  6.Bd3  is equally good, and it sets a trap:  6...Qxd4?  7.Bb5+  , winning the Queen @@StartBracket@@+6.5@@EndBracket@@. }
