1. e4 e6 { French Defense } 2. d4 { Normal Variation } 2... d5 3. Nc3
{ Paulsen Variation } 3... Nf6 { Classical Variation } 4. Bg5
{ Pinning the Knight to the Queen. } 4... Be7 5. e5 { Main Line } 5... Nfd7 6.
Bxe7 Qxe7 7. f4 { Steinitz Variation. So far this is all well known theory. }
7... c5
{ c5  is a key move for Black in a lot of variations. But in this particular case, it is a blunder that was played thousands of times. This is the second most common mistake in the French Defense. }
8. Nb5
{ The Knight launches two threats: A fork on  c7  and a check on  d6  . In both cases, Black will lose his castling rights. }
8... O-O { Objectively the best move. King safety first! } 9. Nc7
{ White will soon be up the exchange @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. } *

