{ Exchange Variation, A typical response of White players who don't like the French Defense. }
3... exd5 4. Nf3 { The following moves are standard developing moves. } 4...
Nf6 5. Bd3 Bd6 6. Qe2+ { A little check to test Black. } 6... Be6
{ Blocking the check. } 7. Ng5
{ Attacking the Bishop on  e6  with the Knight. } 7... O-O
{ A bad move. Black overlooked something. } 8. Nxe6 { Exchanging pieces. } 8...
fxe6 9. Qxe6+
{ Grabbing a free pawn with check!   Black probably thought he could play  Re8  , pinning the Queen to the King. But he failed to see that  9.Qxe6  comes with a check @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@!   And after  9...Kh8  , White should play  10.O-O  or  10.Qh3  in order to avoid their Queen from getting pinned to the King. }
