{ Advance Variation } 3... f6
{ Moving your f-pawn in the early game often is a bad idea.  3...c5  would have been better: attacking the basis of White's pawn chain. }
4. Bd3 fxe5 { Another poor move. Black's kingside is getting weak... } 5. Qh5+
{ Check! } 5... g6
{ 5...Kd7  is the alternative. After  6.Nf3  , White has a significant advantage @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6. Bxg6+
{ The point of Bd3 after Black played f6. If the Bishop is captured, the Queen can capture the Rook. }
6... hxg6
{ 6...Kd7  would have been a better choice. The game could continue with  7.Qxe5  Qf6  8.Qxf6  Nxf6  9.Bd3  @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
