[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 { French Defense } 2. d4 { Normal Variation } 2... d5 3. e5
{ Advance Variation } 3... c5 { Attacking the pawn on  d4  . } 4. c3
{ Defending  d4  . } 4... Nc6 { Attacking  d4  . } 5. Nf3
{ Paulsen Attack, Defending  d4  . } 5... Qb6 { Attacking  d4  once again. } 6.
Bd3
{ Milner-Barry Gambit, Defending  d4  indirectly, as we saw in the previous variation. }
6... cxd4 { Trading a pair of center pawns. } 7. cxd4 Bd7 8. Bc2
{ Defending the pawn on  d4  , since Nxd4 was a threat because of Black's last move. }
8... Bb4+ { Checking the King in this position is a poor move. } 9. Nc3
{ Developing the Knight while blocking the check. White wanted to play this move anyway! }
9... Nge7 { Developing the second Knight, ready to jump to  f5  next move. }
10. O-O Nf5
{ Attacking the pawn on  d4  with a third piece is a mistake in this position. }
11. Bxf5 { Removing one of the attackers. } 11... exf5
{ A blunder!   Instead, Black should have played  11...Bxc3  12.bxc3  exf5  @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
12. Nxd5
{ Capturing an important pawn. White is up a pawn and has control over the center @@StartBracket@@+4.0@@EndBracket@@. }
