Bd3
{ Milner-Barry Gambit, Defending  d4  indirectly, as we will see in the next couple of moves. }
6... cxd4 7. cxd4 Nxd4
{ Black here probably thinks White gave up defending  d4  . But  d4  is still defended tactically!   Continuations like  7...Nge7  8.O-O  Nxd4  or  7...Bb4+  8.Nc3  Nxd4  will obviously lead to similar tactics as described in this variation. }
8. Nxd4 Qxd4
