8. Bxb7 { Capturing the pawn on  b7  , attacking the Rook in the corner. } 8...
h6
{ A tricky move!   9.Ne4  fails to  9...Bf3  10.Rg1  Bxe4  11.Bxe4  c6  , saving the Rook @@StartBracket@@+1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
9. Rg1 { Counter attacking the Bishop. } 9... Bd7
{ Black's best move, with the idea of  10.Nf3?  Bc6  , saving the Rook. } 10.
Nxf7 { White prefers to capture the Rook instead of saving the Knight. } 10...
Kxf7 11. Bxa8
{ White is up the exchange and Black's pawns are shattered @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@. }
