4. Nf3 Bg4 { Pinning the Knight to the Queen. } 5. h3 Bxf3 { Trading pieces. }
6. Qxf3 Nc6
{ A mistake. The Queen is running out of squares after White's next move. } 7.
Bb5 { The only move to get a big advantage, attacking  c6  once more. } 7...
Qb6
{ Defending the Knight on  c6  with the Queen. But this is actually a blunder. }
8. Nd5 { Attacking the Queen while threatening a fork on  c7  . } 8... Qa5
{ Retreating the Queen while keeping an eye on  c7  . } 9. b4
{ Attacking the Queen to get her off the  a5  -  d8  diagonal. } 9... Qxb5
{ Black ran out of options. } 10. Nxc7+
{ A family fork, forking King, Queen and Rook! } 10... Kd8 11. Nxb5
{ Black is lost @@StartBracket@@+9.0@@EndBracket@@. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
