{ Defending the Knight on  c3  while attacking Black's Knight. A suboptimal move. }
7... Bf5
{ Defending the Knight in the center while eyeing on White's Queen with the Bishop. This is the only move that gives Black an advantage @@StartBracket@@-1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Qe3
{ A blunder. White wanted to keep an eye on the Knight on  c3  while pinning Black's Knight to the King.   8.a3  would have been the best move in this position, in view of  8...Bxc3+  9.bxc3  @@StartBracket@@-1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
8... O-O
{ A great move! Black is ready to bring even more pieces into the game @@StartBracket@@-5.0@@EndBracket@@. By practicing a position like this against a strong engine, you will make the most out of it. }
