{ This move and the next ones are not the best moves for White, but they'll lead to an advantage in development. }
3... dxe4 4. Ng5 exd3 5. Bxd3 { White now is ahead in development. } 5... Nf6
{ Some Black players think that the pawn on  h7   is under attack, so they try to defend it with a move like  5...Nf6  ,  5...h6  or  5...g6  . But all these moves have the same problem... }
6. Nxf7 { Forking Queen and Rook, luring the King away from the Queen. } 6...
Kxf7 { 6...Qd5  7.Nxh8  Qxg2  8.Rf1  @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@. } 7.
Bg6+
{ Sacrificing another piece, with a discovered attack at the Black Queen. This is the point of both sacrifices! }
7... hxg6 8. Qxd8
{ White is ahead in material, is still able to castle, and has a nice pawn structure @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@. }
