1. e4 c6 { Caro-Kann Defense } 2. Nf3 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. d4 Bf5 5. Nc3 e6
{ The first poor move in the game. The Bishop on  f5  now can't defend the King anymore. }
6. Bb5+ Nd7
{ A blunder.   After  6...Nc6  7.Ne5  Rc8  , the game is about equal @@StartBracket@@+0.0@@EndBracket@@. }
7. Ne5 { Attacking the Knight on  d7  with a second piece. } 7... Nf6
{ The only way to defend the Knight on  d7  once more. } 8. Bg5
{ Attacking one of the defenders of  d7  , pinning it to the Queen. } 8... Be7
{ Unpinning, defending the Knight on  f6  . } 9. Bxf6
{ Capturing one of the defenders of  d7  . } 9... gxf6
{ Recapturing with the pawn, the best move. } 10. Nxd7
{ Grabbing a free piece, at least for now. } 10... a6
{ The best move. Two of White's pieces are now under attack. } 11. Nxf6+
{ Double check! The King has to step out of the check. } 11... Kf8 12. Nfxd5
{ Other moves are possible as well, but this one simplifies the position. }
12... axb5 13. Nxe7
