1. e4 Nf6 { Alekhine Defense } 2. Nc3 d5
{ Scandinavian Variation, Challenging the pawn on  e4  . } 3. e5
{ Advancing the pawn, attacking the Knight. } 3... Nfd7
{ Retreating the Knight while attacking the pawn on  e5  . The Knight now isn't defending  d5  anymore. }
4. d4 { Defending  e5  . } 4... c5
{ Attacking the base of White's pawn chain. Purposely ignoring the fact that  d5  is undefended. }
