{ Defending against the checkmate threat on  f7  . } 8. e6
{ Renewing the checkmate threat:  8...h6?  9.Qf7+  Qxf7  10.exf7#  , a beautiful David & Goliath mate! }
8... g6
{ With the idea to play Bg7 next move. White lost a piece for a pawn @@StartBracket@@-5.0@@EndBracket@@. }
