Nb6 5. f4 { Four Pawns Attack } 5... dxe5 { Exchanging a pair of pawns. } 6.
fxe5 c5
{ Challenging the base of White's pawn chain. Not the strongest move, but not every White player knows how to get an advantage. }
7. d5 e6
{ Not only challenging the pawn on  d5  , but also threatening a sneaky check on  h4  . }
8. d6
{ A bad move. White failed to see the incoming Queen check.   8.Nc3  will give White an advantage. The Knight covers  e4  , so the tactic from the main variation doesn't work for Black @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
8... Qh4+
