{ Developing the Bishop while attacking one of White's center pawns. } 3. Bd3
{ Defending the pawn on  e4  . } 3... f5
{ Encouraging white to capture the pawn, in order to open up the diagonal for the Bishop on  b7  . }
4. exf5 { Capturing the pawn anyway! White has a trick up his sleeve. } 4...
Bxg2 { Black happily captures the pawn on  g2  . } 5. Qh5+
