Nf6
{ A blunder that will result in checkmate soon.   Black's best move in this position is  6...Bg7  , creating a flight square for the King. After  7.gxh7+  Kf8  8.Nh3!  , the position gets too complicated for the sake of this course. An engine can help you to better understand the position. A possible continuation:  8...Bxh1  9.Ng5  , threatening checkmate on  f7  ,  9...Bd5  10.hxg8=Q+  Bxg8  11.Qf3+  Bf6  12.Qxa8  @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@. }
7. gxh7+
{ A very important move! In similar situations, White's best move was to advance the pawn in order to make a Queen on  h8  . But in this case, White has something even better. }
7... Nxh5 { Capturing the Queen, the only available move. } 8. Bg6#
{ Checkmate! Without a Black pawn on  h7  , White's Bishop can't be captured. }
