{ This Bishop is acting like a tall pawn... } 6... Bc5
{ Developing the Bishop, eyeing on  f2  . } 7. Nge2
{ The most played move in this position is a blunder! } 7... Ng4
{ Attacking  f2  with two pieces. } 8. O-O
{ By far the most played move, making things even worse. } 8... Qh4
{ A strong move with a double purpose: Putting more pressure on  f2  while threatening checkmate on  h2  . }
